OES, No. 3 cans, SI.OO\n6 cans\nDAVIS SPAGHETTI SI.OO\n8 cans\nVIENNA SAUSAGE SI.OO\n8 cans\nCORNED BEEF HASH SI.OO\n8 cans v\nVEAL LOAF S.IOO\n5 cans\nCORNED BEEF SI.OO\n3 cans\nDRIED BEEF SI.OO\n5 glasses\nWe Are Still Hammering Down the Prices\nIN THE GREATEST\nuuffliiunni\nEVER STAGED IN WASHBURN\nJake Yderstad was at his home in\nthe town of Lincoln over Christmas\nvisiting with his family.\nLouis Wcchsmuth of the Bayfield\nProgress was transacting business\nin the city on Tuesday of this week.\nMr. Chas. B. Joanish, of Duluth,\nspent Xmas here at the home of his\nsister Mrs. M. Stapleton.\nJohn A. Jacobs is in the city spend\ning the holidays with his family and\nvisiting old acquaintances?\nGus. Bowers who has been steward\non one of the large lake boats this\nsummer is expected home about\nJan. Ist.\nEd. Moon, wife and two children,\nof Virginia spent the Christmas holi\ndays in the city visiting friends and\nrelatives.\nJohn O'Sullivan Jr. of Madison has\nbeen home for a few days visiting\nwith his parents, Mr. and Mrs. John\nO\u2019Sullivan.\nCounty Judge H. P. Axelberg has\nbeen in Milwaukee this week where\nhe has been attending the State\nCounty Judges Association, which\nopened its annual session Tuesday\nmorning.\nSWEATERS\nOne lot that have\ngot to go\nFormer Price $4.00.\n$1.89\nIjjjjjj jj\nPERSONALS\nTo our old friends, loyal\nand true;--to our valued new\nfriends;-and to those whose\nfriendship we strive to de\nserve; we heartily wish un\nmeasured happiness and good\nfortune throughout the com\ning years.\nGEORGE\n(POX BKOS.) (POX BROS.)\nMiss Evelyn Wright, of Duluth,\narrived in the city Sunday after\nnoon and will visit friends until after\nNew Years.\nFRIENDS\nNot because it is an hon\nored custom, but because\nof the sincerity of our ap\npreciation, we take this\nopportunity to thank you for\nthe part you have played in\nour business prosperity.\nWe wish you joy and happi\nness, unmeasured and unin\nterrupted, during the coming\ntwelve months.\nPETE\n(FOX BROS.) (FOX BROS.)\nFOR RENT\nHouse with 5 rooms, electric\nlights, water. $7.00 per month.\nESTABROOK-DOWNS CO.\nEdw. Jacobs who has been sailing\non the lakes the past summer is\nspending the holidays with his par\nents and friends.\nMrs. H. C. Koenig run a sliver in\nher hand last week and infection set\nin and has been giving her consider\nable trouble and pain.\nIngwald Sylte and wife of Chicago\nhave been in the city during the\npast few days visiting at the home\nof Mr. Sylte\u2019s mother.\nFrank Westing who is living at\nAshland, has been here for several\ndays during the past week visiting\nwith relatives and friends.\nThe infant baby of Mr. and Mrs.\nAlvin Reinstrom passed away on\nWednesday of this week! after a\nshort illness with pneumonia.\nRichard Bering Jr. who is em\nployed at the steel plant at Duluth\ncame down Sunday for a short visit\nwith his parents and friends.\nElmer Olson and family and Mrs.\nGreenwood spent the Christmas holi\ndays at Superior, the guests of Mrs.\nGreenwood\u2019s daughter Mrs. Rock\nwood.\nMr. and Mrs. Charles Marbo and\nson of Minneapolis have been in the\ncity during the holidays visiting at\nthe home of Mrs. Marbo\u2019s parents,\nMr. and Mrs. W. A. Fenton\nONE LOT\nOVERALLS\n$2.50 VALUES\nWhile They Last\n$1.49\nTom Lamoreaux came down from\nNymore, Minn., to spend gie holi\ndays with relatives and friends.\nThe Misses Smiths entertained for\ntheir neices on Tuesday evening of\nthis week. About a dozen young\npeople were present and a pleasant\nevening was spent.\nPercy Lowry who is located at\nDetroit, has been home during the\nholidays, visiting at the home of his\nparents, Mr. and Mrs. Robert Lowry\neast Sixth street.\n\u2014I\nGeorge Anderson, son of Mr. and\nMrs. Erick Anderson former Wash\nburn residents, came up from Detroit\nto spend the holidays with relatives\nand friends in this city,\nMr. and Mrs. T. C. Oscar and\ndaughter Jean of Superior visited in\nthe city over Christmas with rela\ntives and friends. They returned\nhome again Tuesday morning.\nGeorge R. Moore of the Wash\nburn Manufacturing Company left\nduring the past week for Antigo and\nthe east where he will visit with his\ndaughters during the holidays.\n\nThe Kenfield-Lamoreaux plant has\nclosed down for a short period owing\nto general business depression all\nover the country. It is expected\nthat the shut down will not be for a\nvery long time.\nJohn Spitzer left Wednesday morn\ning for. Ewen, Mich., where he will\njoin his wife who has been visiting\nhr relatives there the paist week.\nThey expect to remain away for the\nwinter.\nThe annual installation of officers\nof the K. P. lodge will be held at\ntheir hall next Tuesday evening,\nThe members and their frineds will\nenjoy a smoker and a lunch. All\nvisiting brothers in the city are\nurged to attend.\nOscar J. Caron was in the city a\nfew days this week visiting with re\nlatives and friends. Mr. Caron is\nnow Area Commercial Manager of\nthe Northwestern Telephone Ex\nchange Cos. with headquarters at\nWadena, Minn.\nThe Civic League of Bayfield\nwill give a New Years Eve\ndance, Friday, December 31st,\nat Community Memorial Hall.\nRefreshments will be served.\nPrice of tickets, including was\ntax $1.25. Everybody wel\ncome.\nBOYS CAPS\nAK Sizes, Colors and Shapes\n$2.00, $175 and\n$1.50\n89c\nFAiIfjERS! --1 buy green and\nsalted hides of all kinds and pay\nhighest prices. See me before\nyou sell. JOS. VENO, Omaha St.\nWashburn, Wit. Phone 125-w.\n....THE.,..\nNORTHERN\nSTATE\nBANK\nWASHBURN WIS.\nState Depository\nSTRENGTH SECURITY\nDiamond Well Drilling Cos.\nW. A. GUSTAFSON, Mgr.\nART ANDERSON, Operator\nOffice at Art Anderson\u2019s Res., Pine St.\nWASHBURN, WISCONSIN\n5 Furnished Rooms\nFor Rent\nsls Per Month\nEstabrook-Downs Cos.\nAmos M. Hansen\nFuneral Director\nDay and Night Calls to All Parts\nof the County Promptly\nAttended.\n\nMrs. Amos Hansen\nLady Licensed Embalmer\nFull Automobile\nFuneral Equipment.\nBOYS SUITS\nCorduroy and Moleskin\nSizes 13 to 18\nFormer $15.00 Seller\n$6.89","height":"31662","width":"23301"}}
